   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 3. Log Transform & Scale\n",
    "\n",
    "All skewed features log-transformed, then StandardScaler applied.\n",
    "Scaling is essential for PCA, K-Means, and DBSCAN."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Feature matrix shape: (4338, 14)\n",
      "\n",
      "Features: ['Log_Recency', 'Log_Frequency', 'Log_Monetary', 'Log_Avg_Order_Value', 'Log_Max_Order', 'Log_Std_Order', 'Log_Avg_Items', 'Log_Unique_Products', 'Log_Unique_Categories', 'Log_Active_Weeks', 'Log_Tenure', 'Top_Category_Pct', 'Pct_Weekend', 'Pct_Morning']\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "log_cols = ['Recency','Frequency','Monetary','Avg_Order_Value','Max_Order',\n",
    "            'Std_Order','Avg_Items','Unique_Products','Unique_Categories',\n",
    "            'Active_Weeks','Tenure']\n",
    "for col in log_cols:\n",
    "    customer_df[f'Log_{col}'] = np.log1p(customer_df[col])\n",
    "\n",
    "feature_cols = [f'Log_{c}' for c in log_cols] + \\\n",
    "               ['Top_Category_Pct','Pct_Weekend','Pct_Morning']\n",
    "\n",
    "X        = customer_df[feature_cols].copy()\n",
    "scaler   = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Feature matrix shape: {X_scaled.shape}')\n",
    "print(f'\\nFeatures: {feature_cols}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 4. PCA — Dimensionality Reduction\n",
    "\n",
    "PCA reduces 14 correlated features into uncorrelated components.\n",
    "It tells us:\n",
    "1. How many dimensions actually carry signal\n",
    "2. Which original features drive the most variance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "5 components explain 80% of variance\n",
      "7 components explain 90% of variance\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1300x500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pca_full   = PCA()\n",
    "pca_full.fit(X_scaled)\n",
    "explained  = pca_full.explained_variance_ratio_\n",
    "cumulative = np.cumsum(explained)\n",
    "\n",
    "n_80 = np.argmax(cumulative >= 0.80) + 1\n",
    "n_90 = np.argmax(cumulative >= 0.90) + 1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'{n_80} components explain 80% of variance')\n",
    "print(f'{n_90} components explain 90% of variance')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(13, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].bar(range(1, len(explained)+1), explained,\n",
    "            color='steelblue', edgecolor='white', alpha=0.8)\n",
    "axes[0].plot(range(1, len(explained)+1), explained,\n",
